  "prompt": "Is there a way to sort by the most upvoted answers on Quora?",
  "response": "Yes, you can sort answers on Quora by the most upvoted answers. Here's how:\n\nWhen viewing a question on Quora, you'll see a list of answers. By default, Quora usually shows the answers in the \"Sort by Most Relevant\" order. To sort by the most upvoted answers, follow these steps:\n\n1. Scroll to the top of the answer section on the question page.\n2. Look for the \"Sort by\" dropdown menu, which is usually located to the right of the \"Answers\" heading.\n3. Click on the \"Sort by\" dropdown menu.\n4. Select \"Upvoted\" from the list of sorting options.\n\nThis will reorder the answers so that the ones with the most upvotes appear at the top. Keep in mind that the exact layout and wording might vary slightly depending on whether you're using the Quora website or the mobile app, and whether you've made any customizations to your Quora settings.\n\nIt's worth noting that while sorting by upvotes can be useful for seeing what the Quora community finds most valuable, it's not always the best way to find the most accurate or helpful answer. Sometimes, less upvoted answers can still provide valuable insights or perspectives.",
